episodes.title: Should Andrew face police investigation? Feat. Jennie Bond, Ava Santina & Wilfred | Storm Huntley
episodes.description:
Should Andrew face police investigation?

He was of course known as Prince Andrew until Buckingham Palace announced last night he will be stripped of that title - he's also just now been struck off the peerage roll, effectively meaning he's officially lost his Duke of York title, too.

The family of Virginia Giuffre, the woman who accused Andrew of sexual abuse before she took her own life earlier this year, say she would be celebrating this news.

But her brother Sky Roberts told BBC's Newsnight they want things to go further.

Andrew continues to deny all the allegations Virginia Giuffre made against him, which include sexually abusing her three times when she was 17.

There are also reports that Andrew handed confidential information about Giuffre to his police bodyguard so he could dig up information to use against her - but he has not commented on these claims
